1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
The Sun fuses hydrogen into helium, releasing energy that becomes sunlight.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:07,200
But how does this fusion actually occur?

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:10,000
It all starts deep within its core.

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:14,400
Intense pressure and temperature force hydrogen atoms to collide, overcoming repulsion.

5
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:20,400
This collision creates helium and releases enormous energy in the form of light and heat.

6
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:25,200
This energy travels 93 million miles to reach us, illuminating our days.

7
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,200
Curious about more cosmic wonders?

8
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:30,000
Like and follow for more stellar insights!
